<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The=C2=A0economics of a Paramount Global acqui=
sition are simple but tricky:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Paramount has about <a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2Vj=
Lmdvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvODEzODI4LzAwMDExOTMxMjUyNDEwNTA=
yNi9kNTU4ODE3ZGRlZjE0YS5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBdd2edb33" itemprop=3D=
"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #0000=
00; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bott=
om-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">655=
 million shares outstanding</a>.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">O=
f those 655 million shares, roughly 41 million are Class A shares, which ha=
ve voting rights; the rest are Class B shares, which don=E2=80=99t.</li>=09=
<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The Class A stock trades at=C2=A0$22.37 p=
er share as of=C2=A0Friday=E2=80=99s close; the Class B trades at $11.91. T=
hat gives you a combined equity market capitalization of about $8.2 billion=
.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Figure you=E2=80=99d have to pay=
 a premium to buy the whole company. Let=E2=80=99s say the total equity val=
ue would be $12 billion, roughly a 50% premium to the current price.<a clas=
s=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=3D"color: #000000; text-dec=
oration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0=
00000; border-bottom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent =
!important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But notice that=C2=A0you could ta=
ke over the company =E2=80=94=C2=A0control the shareholder vote, elect new =
directors, vote for a merger, etc. =E2=80=94=C2=A0with just 21 million Clas=
s A shares. That would represent a majority of the Class A voting shares, b=
ut only about 3.2% of the total shares.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: =
5px;">In fact, 31.5 million Class A shares are owned by National Amusements=
, a company controlled by Shari Redstone, the daughter and successor of for=
mer Paramount mogul Sumner Redstone. Those shares represent about 77% of th=
e voting stock, but less than 5% of the total stock.<a class=3D"footnote-in=
dex" href=3D"#footnote-2" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; disp=
lay: inline-block;">
<span>[2]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If you want to acquire Paramount,=
 how much should you offer to pay for Redstone=E2=80=99s Class A stock? For=
 the other Class A stock? For the Class B stock?</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Assume that you are willing to pay $12 billion=
 of total equity value for the company, and that you will be compelled by c=
ompetitive pressures to pay that amount. Two=C2=A0possible answers suggest =
themselves:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The=C2=A0<em>fairest=C2=A0</em>answer=
 is that if you are willing to pay $12 billion for the equity, you should p=
ay about $18.32 per share,<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-3" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !importan=
t; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[3]</span>
</a>=C2=A0treating the A and B shares the same, since they have the same ec=
onomic rights.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-4" style=3D"col=
or: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bo=
rder-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; backgroun=
d-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[4]</span>
</a>=C2=A0This represents about a 54% premium to the trading price of the C=
lass B shares, but about an 18%=C2=A0<em>discount=C2=A0</em>to the trading =
price of the Class A shares.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The=
=C2=A0<em>least fair=C2=A0</em>answer is that if you are willing to pay $12=
 billion for the equity, you should pay=C2=A0<em>all=C2=A0</em>of it to Sha=
ri Redstone, because her voting stock is enough to control the company. Pay=
 her $380.95 per share for her Class A shares,<a class=3D"footnote-index" h=
ref=3D"#footnote-5" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: none !important; background-color: transparent !important; display: i=
nline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>=C2=A0give everyone else zero, boom, you control the company. She gets =
about a 1,600% premium to the last trade; everyone else gets a 100% discoun=
t.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Neither of those answers is really feasible: Y=
ou=E2=80=99re not going to get the Class A holders to vote to sell their sh=
ares at a discount, and if you announce a plan to buy Redstone=E2=80=99s sh=
ares and stiff everyone else, Paramount=E2=80=99s board =E2=80=94=C2=A0whic=
h has fiduciary duties to all shareholders =E2=80=94 will try to stop you.=
=C2=A0(The board of Paramount=E2=80=99s predecessor=C2=A0<a href=3D"https:/=
/link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxv=
b21iZXJnLmNvbS92aWV3L2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTgtMDUtMTUvY2JzLXdhbnRzLXRvLWdldC1yaWQ=
tb2YtYS1zaGFyZWhvbGRlcj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNDI5MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPW=
VtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA0MjkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduP=
W1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf18e96cb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">once tried to</a>=
=C2=A0<em>take away=C2=A0</em>Redstone=E2=80=99s votes, arguing that was in=
 the best interests of other shareholders.) And if you just buy Redstone=E2=
=80=99s shares, take control and leave the Class B and minority Class A sha=
res outstanding, they will=C2=A0stick around and make various sorts of econ=
omic and legal trouble.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-6" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; =
background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[6]</span>
</a></p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But those are the boundaries, and then you hav=
e to find the right place on the curve between them. You have to give Redst=
one enough for her shares to make it worth her while, and you have to give =
everyone else enough that the board will let you do it. And, in a competiti=
ve auction, different bidders might strike the balance in different ways; R=
edstone might end up favoring the more Redstone-friendly bidder, while the =
board might end up favoring the more Class B-friendly one.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDQtMDcvZGlzdHJlc3NlZC1kZWJ0LWRlYWwtbWFrZXMtcGVvcGxlLW1h=
ZD9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNDI5MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U=
9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA0MjkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07=
ceef4b8524a319a23cB52ff3e1c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope"=
 target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importan=
t; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-st=
yle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">talk sometimes</a> about my simple mod=
el of distressed debt investing: If you=E2=80=99re a company with $100 of d=
ebt outstanding, you go to the holders of 51% of it and say =E2=80=9Cwe=E2=
=80=99ll pay you back 105 cents on the dollar if you vote to stiff the othe=
r guys.=E2=80=9D So you pay $53.55 to the majority and $0 to the minority a=
nd come out ahead. That doesn=E2=80=99t=C2=A0<em>really=C2=A0</em>work, but=
 it=E2=80=99s the schematic intuition behind lots of other things (=E2=80=
=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35199213.256350=
/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDQtMDkvYS=
1tZW1lLXN0b2NrLWZvci1wcml2YXRlLWNvbXBhbmllcz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNDI5MjRfTU9ORVlTV=
FVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA0=
MjkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf735f142" item=
prop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color=
: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; bord=
er-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #cc=
c;">non-pro rata uptiering</a>,=E2=80=9D etc.) that do work.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">We <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusin=
ess.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL=
2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDUtMjQvZGVidC1pcy10cmlja2llci10aGFuLWVxdWl0eT9jbXBpZD1C=
QkQwNDI5MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHR=
lciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA0MjkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a3=
19a23cB87b8eb9e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_=
blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bo=
ttom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; =
background-color: #ccc;">also</a> talk <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcG=
luaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMDIvbWVyZ2Vycy1hcmVuLXQtYWx3YXlzLWZhaXI_Y21wa=
WQ9QkJEMDQyOTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3Ns=
ZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNDI5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB3fe49cb0" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">sometimes</a> about how it=E2=80=99s harder t=
o pull off this sort of thing in=C2=A0<em>equity=C2=A0</em>deals (like merg=
ers): Getting 51% of <em>bondholders</em> to vote to stiff the other 49% is=
 endlessly popular, but getting 51% of=C2=A0<em>shareholders=C2=A0</em>to v=
ote to stiff the other 49% is not really allowed; there are fiduciary dutie=
s and protections and expectations that all shareholders will get treated f=
airly.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, at Paramount you can contro=
l of 100% of the company by buying 5% of the stock. Of course that is a tem=
ptation.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Wall Street Journal <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNv=
bS9idXNpbmVzcy9tZWRpYS9wYXJhbW91bnQtcmVkc3RvbmUtbWVyZ2VyLWJha2lzaC0xNjJjZDg=
1ND9tb2Q9aHBfbGVhZF9wb3M3/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6b6b346e" itemprop=3D"St=
oryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000;=
 text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-=
color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">checks=
 in on Paramount=E2=80=99s deal talks</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">When David Ellison, the CEO of production comp=
any Skydance Media and son of billionaire Larry Ellison, raised the idea of=
 a merger, [Shari] Redstone was ready to hand over a media empire her famil=
y has controlled for nearly four decades. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Paramount has been in exclusive talks with Sky=
dance toward a deal that would net Redstone more than $2 billion in cash fo=
r National Amusements, the holding company that owns the family=E2=80=99s 7=
7% voting stake in Paramount and a chain of movie theaters. Nonvoting Param=
ount investors would get stock in a newly merged company.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The current value of Redstone=E2=80=99s Paramo=
unt holding is about $750 million, meaning she would be getting a substanti=
al premium in a Skydance deal.=C2=A0=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">An independent board committee has been tasked=
 with reviewing the Skydance deal. In a statement, National Amusements said=
 it would respect the committee=E2=80=99s decision on =E2=80=9Cwhether the =
Skydance deal presents an attractive transaction for Paramount and whether =
they want to continue to move forward.=E2=80=9D National Amusements has sig=
naled that it is open to making a transaction contingent on approval by a m=
ajority of non-Redstone shareholders, people close to the talks said.=C2=A0=
</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Paramount has another potential option on the =
table. Private-equity giant Apollo Global Management submitted a $26 billio=
n offer, including about $12 billion in equity plus assumption of debt. =E2=
=80=A6 An Apollo deal could be much more appealing to Paramount shareholder=
s=E2=80=94giving them a cash payout=E2=80=94but wouldn=E2=80=99t give Redst=
one the hefty premium Skydance is offering.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The proposed Skydance deal involves (1) paying=
 Redstone cash for National Amusements (and, thus, the controlling block of=
 Class A shares) and (2)=C2=A0<em>not=C2=A0</em>paying cash for the rest of=
 the non-controlling shares:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The deal itself would be structured in two ste=
ps. First, Skydance, which is backed by the Ellison family, and private-equ=
ity firms KKR and RedBird Capital Partners, would buy out National Amusemen=
ts. Then, Paramount would acquire Skydance with stock at a valuation of $5 =
billion.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The valuation has turned heads since the Journ=
al first reported on Skydance=E2=80=99s financials. The company=E2=80=99s e=
xpected revenue this year of just over $1 billion is one-thirtieth of Param=
ount=E2=80=99s and it is expected to generate earnings before interest, tax=
es, depreciation and amortization of $90 million.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Right I mean there is some economic pie to be =
divided up here, and 95% of the shares have no voting power. If you make a =
good deal with the person who owns the controlling 5%, you can get a good d=
eal for yourself too.</p>
