<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Freedom of speech</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As a matter of US constitutional law, the argu=
ment =E2=80=9CI should be allowed to commit securities fraud because of fre=
edom of speech and the First Amendment=E2=80=9D is=C2=A0wrong,=C2=A0but it =
has a respectable intellectual pedigree. You can see its appeal. The US Sec=
urities and Exchange Commission <em>does=C2=A0</em>pretty intrusively regul=
ate speech, in a way that would not be acceptable in most areas of US law. =
And if the First Amendment protects anything, it <a href=3D"https://link.ma=
il.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJn=
LmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMTUtMTEtMDYvZXh4b24tbWlnaHQtYmUtaW4tdHJvdWJ=
sZS1vdmVyLWNsaW1hdGUtY2hhbmdlP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MjkyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZW=
RpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQyOSZ1dG1fY2Ftc=
GFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBd6a433d8" itemprop=3D"StoryL=
ink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; tex=
t-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-colo=
r: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">protects t=
he right to lie</a> to the public. But not about securities.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">On the other hand, the composition of the US c=
ourts is changing;=C2=A0they are becoming more skeptical of regulatory agen=
cies=C2=A0and more receptive to arguments that regulatory restrictions on f=
reedom are unconstitutional. It=E2=80=99s worth trying, every now and then,=
 to see if the US Supreme Court might change its mind and decide that, actu=
ally, freedom of speech=C2=A0<em>does=C2=A0</em>require the right to commit=
 securities fraud.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGlj=
bGVzLzIwMjQtMDQtMjkvc3VwcmVtZS1jb3VydC1yZWplY3RzLW11c2stcy10d2l0dGVyLXNpdHR=
lci1hcHBlYWwtaW4tc2VjLXdpbj9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNDI5MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaX=
VtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA0MjkmdXRtX2NhbXBha=
WduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB656f0374" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Not today tho=
ugh</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The US Supreme Court rejected an appeal from E=
lon Musk in his =E2=80=9CTwitter sitter=E2=80=9D case, leaving intact his a=
greement with the Securities and Exchange Commission to have an in-house la=
wyer pre-approve his social media posts about Tesla Inc.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The justices, without comment, refused to hear=
 contentions from the Tesla chief executive officer that the accord he sign=
ed in 2018 now violates his constitutional free speech rights.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Musk has battled the SEC over his social media=
 posts since he tweeted in August 2018 that he had =E2=80=9Cfunding secured=
=E2=80=9D to take Tesla private, sending shares of the electric carmaker su=
rging.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The regulator claimed in a lawsuit the followi=
ng month that Musk misled shareholders with that post. Two days later, Musk=
 settled with the SEC, agreeing to resign as Tesla chairman and pay $20 mil=
lion as part of the deal. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The agreement is a =E2=80=9Cquintessential pri=
or restraint that the law forbids,=E2=80=9D Musk=E2=80=99s lawyers argued i=
n the Supreme Court appeal. =E2=80=9CThe pre-approval provision at issue co=
ntinues to cast an unconstitutional chill over Mr. Musk=E2=80=99s speech wh=
enever he considers making public communications.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">They are not=C2=A0<em>exactly=C2=A0</em>wrong,=
 but they are wrong enough. The SEC really is in the business of chilling E=
lon Musk from saying stuff about Tesla=E2=80=99s stock, and that=E2=80=99s =
fine.</p>
