om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Low rates phenomena</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusi=
ness.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9u=
L2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDEtMTgvY29pbmJhc2UtdHJhZGVzLWJlYW5pZS1iYWJpZXM_Y21waWQ=
9QkJEMDQyOTI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZX=
R0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNDI5JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524=
a319a23cB5eb9138c" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D=
"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-=
bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid=
; background-color: #ccc;">straightforward story</a> you could tell about r=
ecent financial history is that interest rates were low for a very long tim=
e, which meant=C2=A0that discount rates were low, which meant that a dollar=
 in the distant future was pretty much as good as a dollar right now, which=
 meant that investors were willing to put their money into risky bets with =
no expectation of any cash flows anytime soon. Thus a huge boom in the valu=
ations of speculative private tech companies. Thus the =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"=
https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d=
3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMTEtMDcvbW92aWVwYXNzLXdh=
cy1ub3QtYS1nb29kLWJ1c2luZXNzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA0MjkyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWR=
pdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQyOSZ1dG1fY2FtcG=
FpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB5b8f311d" itemprop=3D"StoryLi=
nk" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text=
-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color=
: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">
MoviePass economy</a>,=E2=80=9D where venture capitalists were willing to i=
nvest billions in companies that lost money on every transaction, in the ho=
pe that one day those companies would achieve enough scale to stop doing th=
at. And thus crypto, where markets gave huge valuations to speculative toke=
ns without even a plan to one day have cash flows.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">And then rates went up and that all evaporated=
. At the Wall Street Journal, James Mackintosh <a href=3D"https://link.mail=
.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9maW=
5hbmNlL3N0b2Nrcy9mb3JnZXQtbW9vbnNob3RzLWludmVzdG9ycy13YW50LXByb2ZpdC1ub3ctM=
Tk3ODdmMjU/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7d66ef9e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemsc=
ope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoratio=
n: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000;=
 border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">wrote yesterday</a> t=
hat now =E2=80=9Cinvestors want a clear route to a return on corporate cash=
 sunk into new projects,=E2=80=9D and =E2=80=9Cmoney that flooded into risk=
y ventures that won=E2=80=99t pay dividends for years, if ever, was much mo=
re acceptable when interest rates were near zero than when the alternative =
is a Treasury yielding almost 5%.=E2=80=9D=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This strikes me as basically a correct story, =
but artificial intelligence spending=C2=A0is maybe an exception? <a href=3D=
"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6Ly93=
d3cud3NqLmNvbS90ZWNoL2FpL2ludmVzdG9ycy1hcmUtc2hvd2VyaW5nLWFpLXN0YXJ0dXBzLXd=
pdGgtY2FzaC1vbmUtcHJvYmxlbS10aGV5LWRvbnQtaGF2ZS1tdWNoLW9mLWEtYnVzaW5lc3MtOT=
Q1MzRmYzk_bW9kPWhwX2xpc3RhX3BvczM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBafb00406" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
">The Journal also reports</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Despite a broad downturn in the startup sector=
, investors chasing the stock market successes of Nvidia and Microsoft have=
 deluged AI upstarts with record levels of funding, minting dozens of compa=
nies with billion-dollar valuations in the past year. The investment frenzy=
 is already fueling concerns of a bubble as startups struggle to translate =
the hype into revenue.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CEveryone believes that AI is the futu=
re, so we are going to see an extraordinary amount of investment until prov=
en otherwise,=E2=80=9D said Alex Clayton, a general partner at the venture =
firm Meritech. =E2=80=9CThe problem is that we don=E2=80=99t know what thes=
e business models are going to look like at scale. You can have theories ab=
out it, but you really don=E2=80=99t know.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Fears of rising startup valuations aren=E2=80=
=99t new in Silicon Valley. But the AI gold rush is notable because investo=
rs are writing massive checks=E2=80=94sometimes in the hundreds of millions=
 of dollars=E2=80=94just to get these companies off the ground. Even during=
 the peak of the startup boom, such large financings were reserved for late=
r-stage private companies gearing up for aggressive growth. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Imbue hit a valuation of more than $1 billion =
with its fundraising last year, courting backers like Nvidia and ex-Google =
CEO Eric Schmidt. Chief Executive Kanjun Qiu dazzled investors with a visio=
n to build intelligent computers that could give humans the =E2=80=9Cfreedo=
m, dignity, and agency to do the things we love.=E2=80=9D Last November, sh=
e lavished her employees with a company off-site to Japan.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Imbue is plowing its cash into developing AI m=
odels that it hopes will one day create autonomous AI agents. A company spo=
kesperson said it made a =E2=80=9Cdeliberate strategic decision=E2=80=9D no=
t to commercialize in order to focus on research and that investors were on=
 board with this approach.=C2=A0</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">One model of this is =E2=80=9Cartificial gener=
al intelligence (AGI) will be so enormously lucrative, and so soon, that yo=
ur business plans and=C2=A0discount rate don=E2=80=99t=C2=A0matter all that=
 much.=E2=80=9D Sometimes, though, I think about OpenAI=E2=80=99s <a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/35199213.256350/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMTEtMjAvd2hvLWNvbnRy=
b2xzLW9wZW5haT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwNDI5MjRfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV=
0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yNDA0MjkmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3=
R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBcdf7966f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">great warning to potenti=
al investors</a> that =E2=80=9Cit would be wise to view any investment in O=
penAI Global, LLC in the spirit of a donation, with the understanding that =
it may be difficult to know what role money will play in a post-AGI world.=
=E2=80=9D If your discounted cash flow model is, like, =E2=80=9CYear 1: spe=
nd $1 billion, Year 2: spend $2 billion, Year 3: a paradise of universal ab=
undance in which money no longer has uses,=E2=80=9D maybe that just breaks =
Excel?</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also crypto is pretty back, so there=E2=80=99s=
 that.</p>
